description: Derived from GP, initialism of general-purpose. Noun from General Purpose Vehicle (military light utility truck).

entries.meaning: (military) Pertaining to utility or general purpose.
A small, blocky, military-style vehicle with four-wheel drive, suited to rough terrain.
A light utility truck from WWII used by the U.S. Army, and subsequently turned into the trademark Jeep when civilianized by originating manufacturer Willys-Overland.
(genericized trademark) A sport utility vehicle or similar four-wheel-drive vehicle.

verbs.description: jeep (third-person singular simple present jeeps, present participle jeeping, simple past and past participle jeeped)

examples: From there we jeeped over extraordinarily difficult roads to Marwari City, the site of Southern Philippine University, where I had been invited to address a convocation on the subject of "College Life in the United States."

description: Disputed. Possibly from Eugene the Jeep, a character in Popeye cartoons.

entries.meaning: (corrosion) A device for detecting discontinuity in a protective coating, also called a "holiday detector"
(Australia, regional) A covered shopping cart, also called a "shopping stroller".
